                    <p>
                        Marieke is a former student who interned at Active Collective. Pim is the co-founder of Digitaal
                        Toegankelijk. They told
                        us about their insights on the importance of digital accessibility.
                    </p>

                    <h3>Who likes to be excluded?</h3>
                    <p>
                        Nobody likes to be excluded, but it happens unintentionally due to bad accessibility in digital
                        content.
                    </p>



                    <p>
                        While designing, ask yourself these questions:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Can everyone perceive this content?
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Can everyone access and use this content?
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Can everyone understand this content?
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Is the technology behind my digital product semantically correct?
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        WCAG (Web Content Accessibility Guidelines) are guidelines for making websites accessible. WCAG
                        has
                        4 main
                        principles(P.O.U.R.):
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Perceivable
                        </li>
                        <li>Operable</li>
                        <li>Understandable</li>
                        <li>Robust</li>
                    </ul>

